{"questionId":"12646","questionHtml":"<p>Find the size of&nbsp;angle <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\\mathop {\\text{C}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{D}}\"><mtext>A</mtext><mover><mtext>C</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>D</mtext></math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>(ACD = ) 70° − (180° − 125° − 31.9478°…)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for subtracting their angle <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\\mathop {\\text{C}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{B}}\"><mtext>A</mtext><mover><mtext>C</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>B</mtext></math></span> from 70°.</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>(ADC =) 360 − (85 + 70 + 125) = 80</p>\n<p>(ACD =) 180 − 80 − 53.0521...&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>46.9°&nbsp; (46.9478…°) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em>(ft)<em>(G2)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Follow through from part (b)(i).</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12646","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ2.T_2c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the size of angle AC^D.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Prior learning","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}